HLS 26RS-6308 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 398
BY REPRESENTATIVE FREEMAN
SCHOOLS/EMPLOYEES: Requests that the state Department of Education study the costs
associated with criminal background checks for teachers and other school employees
and submit a written report to the House Committee on Education by March 1, 2027
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request the state Department of Education to study the costs associated with
3 criminal background checks for teachers and other school employees and to submit
4 a written report of findings and conclusions, including any recommendations for
5 related legislation, to the House Committee on Education not later than March 1,
6 2027.
7 WHEREAS, state law provides relative to criminal background checks for teachers
8 and other school employees for the purposes of both certification and employment; and
9 WHEREAS, relative to employment generally, R.S. 15:587.1 requires the employer
10 of anyone who has been given, or has applied to be considered for, a position of supervisory
11 or disciplinary authority over children to request in writing that the bureau of criminal
12 identification and information supply information to ascertain whether that person has been
13 arrested for or convicted of, or pled nolo contendere to, any criminal offense; and
14 WHEREAS, relative to the employment of teachers and other school employees, R.S.
15 17:15 requires each city, parish, and other local public school board to establish
16 requirements and procedures consistent with the provisions of R.S. 15:587.1 to determine
17 whether applicants or employees have been arrested for or convicted of, or pled nolo
18 contendere to, any criminal offense; this law also applies to charter schools; and
19 WHEREAS, relative to certification, R.S. 17:8.9 authorizes the state Department of
20 Education to charge a criminal history record check processing fee not to exceed twenty-five
